    Eomer, Sister-Son of Theoden x1<br>
    Frodo, Tired Traveller x1 (extra)<br>
    *Elite Rider x1 (starting)<br>
<br>
Shadow<br>
  From the Starter:<br>
    Broad-Bladed Sword x3<br>
    Ferocity x2<br>
    Orthanc Warrior x3<br>
    minus Still They Came -x2<br>
    Uruk Defender x2<br>
    Uruk Fanatic x3<br>
    Uruk Rear Guard x2<br>
    Uruk Regular x2<br>
    Uruk Stalker x3<br>
    <a href="javascript:card_browser(53)">Uruk-hai Raiding Party</a> x3<br>
  Add-ins:<br>
    Uruk Crossbowman x1<br>
    Uruk Pursuer x1<br>
    Uruk Plains Runner x1<br>
    Dunlending Brigand x1<br>
    Wild Man of Dunland x1<br>
    Southron Soldier x1<br>
    Easterling Infantry x1    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> OK - Anyone see any rares in this deck? There are no rares - and only two uncommon cards that did not already come in the starters (fortress and wild man). <br>
<br>
All the rares I pulled could not be used. They needed to spot Gandalf, an elf, a dwarf, a ring-bound man, etc... most all the other cards I got could not be used either - much the same, need to spot something I didn&#39;t have in order to play.<br>
<br>
Just to make the 30 card min per side I got to stick in the duplicate Frodo! <br>
<br>
On the Shadow half, I decided to put every minion I had into the deck and fill out the rest with Uruk swords and pumps. I ended up with 25 minions, three swords, and two pumps. I actually won three of the four games by overwhelming/killing my opponent.<br>
<br>
I named the deck &quot;Ride into Death&quot; from the very start. I went first every game. My bid was kind of high (3-4) and I won every bid except the first (but I still went first in that game too). With my site 1 out, I rode to site four in the first turn of my first game. I thought, &quot;What the Heck - I&#39;ll do what my stupid deck should do and &#39;ride into death&#39;&quot;. After I survived the first wild ride, I crept the rest of the way until my opponent was killed trying to catch up.<br>
<br>
The site switches I made were also really helpful. In all the other games, I went first and stopped at two - my opponent went to three. It messed up the other Theoden decks that were planning on getting to pull out Theoden and set up the rest for my site four which gave me mass twighlight moving to my battleground/cheap uruk site 5. (I got the different site 3 and 4 from my booster packs.)<br>
<br>
I started the Elite Rider and Eowyn for a few reasons. I only had one of each of these cards; the Elite Rider rocks in sealed deck; and I had two copies of both of the other mains. This was one of the reason I guess I won - I had the Theoden starter, but did not rely on the whimpy Theoden at all.<br>
<br>
The way I won was pure strategy and some good ol&#39; luck. I used Eowyn to her full ability and played around with the ability of the mounted riders and Elite Rider a lot. My shadow side kicked in at 5 as the unprepared opponent ran up the sites to try and outrun me. The Uruk Pursuer totally wrecked the Aragorn decks when played at the right time with just enough swarm to knock out Merry and Pippen for good. Going first gave me a lead in the sites so I could move slower and set myself up more for the later rush. Also, it messed up the decks that expected to pull Aragorn.<br>
<br>
So, even with the dubbed &quot;worst of all starters&quot; and a pathetic draw on Rares and other deck helpers, I &#39;rode into death&#39; and just kept on going.<br>
<br>
d-mail and other comments welcomed!<br>
